<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-8324] User constructed RocksObjects leak memory</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-8324</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Some of the RocksDB options a user can set when extending RocksDBConfigSetter&#160;take Rocks objects as parameters. Many of these &#8211; including potentially large objects like Cache and Filter &#8211; inherit from AbstractNativeReference and must be closed explicitly in order to free the memory of the backing C++ object. However the user has no way of closing any objects they have created in RocksDBConfigSetter, and we do not&#160;ever close them for them.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;KIP-453:&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/KAFKA/KIP-453%3A+Add+close%28%29+method+to+RocksDBConfigSetter&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/KAFKA/KIP-453%3A+Add+close%28%29+method+to+RocksDBConfigSetter&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
